                    <blockquote>
                        <p><br>
                        <font face="Arial" size="5">Welcome to Astro286 - Exoplanets course  </font></p>
                        <p><font size="3" face="Arial"> <b> Instructor:<a href="http://www.astro.ucla.edu/~snaoz/">  Smadar Naoz </a></b></font></p>
                         <p><font size="3" face="Arial"> <b> Reader:<a href="http://www.pa.ucla.edu/directory/emily-martin">  Emily Martin </a></b></font></p>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Arial">The class takes place on Tuesdays and Thursdays 2:00pm - 4:00pm. Home-Work assignments are mandatory and will be 35% of the final grade. There will be a final project - more details will follow. </font></p> 
 <p><font size="2" face="Arial">A summary of the above information and the syllabus can be found <a href="syllabus.pdf"> here</a> </font></p>


<p>
<font face="Arial" size="3" color="#660033"> <b> Final Project</b> </fount><br>

<font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000">Suggested papers: </font> <br>
<ul> <li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2014ApJ...785..126K"> Friends of Hot Jupiters I</a> Knutson et al 2014 </li>

<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1996Sci...274..954R"> planet-planet scattering</a> Rasio and Ford 1996 </li>

<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2009ApJ...703.1131H"> Terrestrial Planets from a Narrow Annulus</a> Hansen 2009 </li>


<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2011Natur.475..206W"> The Grand Tack</a> Walsh et al 2011 </li>



<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1977MNRAS.180...57W"> Aerodynamics  in the solar nebula</a> Weidenschilling 1977 </li>

<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2006ApJ...638..314D"> Dust Growth and Settling</a> 
D'Alessio et al 2006 </li>


<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1996Natur.380..606L"> Orbital migration  51 Pegasi b </a> 
Li et al 1996 </li>


<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1986ApJ...309..846L"> Orbital migration   </a> 
Li and Papaloizou 1986 </li>


<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2003ApJ...585.1024G"> Eccentricity Evolution in Gaseous Disks   </a> 
Goldreich and Sari 2003</li>


<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2004ApJ...614..497G"> Final Stages of Planet Formation  </a> 
Goldreich et al 2004</li>



<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2008ApJ...673..502K"> The Snow Line and  Giant Planets </a> 
Kennedy and  Kenyon 2008</li>


<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2005ApJ...620..459Y"> Streaming Instabilities in Protoplanetary Disks </a> 
Youdin and  Goodman 2005</li>


<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2005ApJ...621L..69R"> Gravitational Instability and Giant Planets  </a> 
Rafikov 2005</li>


<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2006AJ....131.1837K"> Terrestrial Planets Formation  </a> 

Kenyon and  Bromley 2006</li>


<li><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000000"><a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1996Icar..124...62P"> Giant Planets Formation via Accretion  </a> 
Pollack et al 1996</li>

</ul>
</p>

                        <p><font face="Arial" size="5">Recommended reading </font></p>
                       
                        <p><font size="2" face="Arial">
                       <b> Textbooks (not required) </b>
                       <ul>
                           <li> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Astrophysics-Planet-Formation-Philip-Armitage/dp/1107653088/">Astrophysics of Planet Formation</a> by Phil Armitage  </li>
                            <li> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Solar-System-Dynamics-Carl-Murray/dp/0521575974/">Solar System Dynamics</a> by Murray and Dermott </li>
                            <li> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Exoplanets-Space-Science-Sara-Seager/dp/0816529450/">Exoplanets</a> (a collection of reviews) by Sara Seager</li>
                           </ul>
                        <b> Review articles  </b>
                        <ul>
                            <li> <a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2011ARA%26A..49..195A">Dynamics of Protoplanetary Disks</a> by Phil Armitage  </li>
                             <li> <a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2010AREPS..38..493C">Forming Planetesimals in Solar and Extrasolar Nebulae</a> by Chiang and Youdin  </li>
                             <li> <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1208.4694">Building Terrestrial Planets</a> by Morbidelli et al.  </li>
                             <li> <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1009.1738">Keplerian Orbits and Dynamics of Exoplanets</a> by Murray and Correia  </li>
                             <li> <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1311.6816">The Long-Term Dynamical Evolution of Planetary Systems</a> by Davies et al.  </li>
                             
                            </ul>
                        
                        </font></p>
